com.pb.sawdust.util.collections

Class IndexedElement<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.util.collections.IndexedElement<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of the element this IndexedElement instance holds.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<IndexedElement<E>>

    public class IndexedElement<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<IndexedElement<E>>
    The IndexedElement class is used to wrap an object with an integer index. It provides a means for an order or heirarchy to be placed on an object (element) irrespective of that object's characteristics.
